               <floruit notBefore="1800" notAfter="1850"> She was a female leader and warrior in <placeName ref="LOC6185Wallo">Wallo</placeName>. 
                  She was one of the wives of <persName ref="PRS1684AliAbb">ʾAli “ʾAbbā Bullā”</persName> of the Mammadočč dynasty which was the most 
                  powerful ruling family in <placeName ref="LOC6185Wallo">Wallo</placeName> at the beginning of the 19th century.  
                  After the death of her husband in <date>1852</date>, she emerged as an important political figure acting as a regent 
                  to her young son <persName ref="PRS1782AmadeAl">ʾAmade ʾAli</persName>. She played an active part in the resistance of
                  <placeName ref="LOC6185Wallo">Wallo</placeName> to <persName ref="PRS9434Tewodros">Tewodros II</persName>. </floruit>
                  
